# finding-the-area-of-the-triangle-python-

# Let's start adding the 3 main input for the user to enter the the values 

first_value = float(input('Enter first value : '));
second_value = float(input('Enter second value:'));
third_value = float(input('enter the the third value:'));

# now first we need to calculate the semi-permiter to find the area 
# we need to add all the value and dived by two to find the semi perimeter 

sp=(first_value + second_value + third_value) /2

#now we can calculate the area 
area = (sp*(sp-a)*(sp-b)*(sp-c)) ** 0.5 

# now the last step we need to print out the vlaue 

print('The area of the triangle is %0.2f' %area) 
